name: concrete production, 37MPa, for civil engineering, with cement, Portland | concrete, 37MPa | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/13129/documentation

This datasets contains the production of concrete for de-icing salt contact with cement CEM I from primary aggregates (no input of recycled gravel or sand). This concrete is humidified and contains reinforcement steel or other metals. It is exposed to air and humidity as well as forst-dew cycles and chloride-containing water/deicing agents (spray mist).;Density: 2400 kg/m3, content of cement: 310 kg/m3;Exposition class according to EN 206-1: XC4, XD1, XF4;Examples of this exposition class are vertical or horizontal esterior building parts under direct weathering (exposed to rain, frost, deicing agents (as spray mist) such as construction elements of bridges with spray water, concrete ceilings, park decks, sole bathes.

The activity starts with the ingredients for the concrete at the factory gate.

Includes the whole manufacturing processes to produce ready-mixed concrete, internal processes (transport, etc.) and infrastructure. No administration is included.
